args: The White Sparrow Corps secured a victory in\ntheir first battle on the Milon Plains.
Thrown off balance, the imperial forces engaged in\na large-scale retreat. Meanwhile, the Sparrows\njoined up with reinforcements led by the prince.

Capitalizing on the opportunity, the New Alberian
forces take the offensive and begin an advance
on the Empire's position in the southwestern
portion of the Milon Plains.
Leif? Patia? I heard about your actions in\nthe Milon Plains. Extraordinary work.

Driving off the imperial army is no small
feat, especially considering their superior
numbers. The White Sparrow Corps never
fails to inspire wonder.
You give us too much credit, Highness.\nOur victory was thanks to the additional\nstrength we were afforded by the militia.
If I may, Your Highness, you might\nconsider awarding them with medals\nof valor once our work is done here.
You're the New Alberian army, right?!\nOh, thank heavens I found you!
Please help us! Our village! Those men!
Soft, my good woman. Pray gather your\nthoughts, then tell us how we might be\nof assistance to you.

Y-yes, of course. I'm from a small village
to the east where our people have long
suffered under the tyrannical rule of an
imperial nobleman.
When we heard the New Alberian army\nwas coming to liberate the region,\nwe took that moment to revolt!
But our plans were discovered, and before\nwe could take up arms, the imperial army\nswooped down upon us.
We're dug in, but the town is surrounded.\nIt's only a matter of time before they\nlaunch an assault and kill us all!
I need numbers. How many revolutionaries\nare there, and how many imperials?
Um... There's maybe fifty of us, all told,\nand probably a few more imperials.
Your Highness? Captain Leif? Please leave\nthe matter of the village to me.
I can't let you do this alone, Patia.
Forgive me, sire, but we cannot afford to\ndelay the advance of our main force.
I can handle this. The imperial numbers\nshow they're expecting a fight against a\nhandful of amateurs, not professionals.
Patia is right, Your Highness. You must\ncontinue to lead the main force.
Very well, Patia. But I'd like Elly to\naccompany you, if she's agreeable.
Of course. We will set out at once.
Those damned imperials are just sitting\nthere! Do they mean to starve us out?
Oh, they'll come for us soon enough.\nWe never should have taken up arms\nagainst them. We were such fools!
If we surrender now, they might decide\nto show us mercy!
The entire village is surrounded,\njust as the woman said.
And all we have are you, me, and two\nother White Sparrows. Are you certain\nwe can win with these numbers?
Oh, we'll win—I'll make sure of it.\nHowever, before we act, I need to\nknow the conditions in the village.
Look there, Patia. Villagers are spilling\nout of that building.
None of them seem to be armed.\nPerhaps they're planning to surrender?
Bah! I won't let that happen!
I am Vice Captain Patia of the White\nSparrow Corps, and I have come to\nsave this village!
Your village is in a critical position for\nthe Empire! You must fight to hold it!
Wait, OUR village? We're nothing but\na speck on the map.

Perhaps that was the case before, but if
we turn this village into a supply point for
New Alberia, it will endanger the Empire's
base further down the road.
That's why they want you to surrender.\nBut if you turn them back—if you endure—\nit will be a great victory for New Alberia!
Victory is at hand, and we will fight at\nyour side until it is won. Now find the\njustice that stirs in your hearts and fight!
If we make it through this,\nwe'll finally be free...
If our little village is that important,\nI'll fight for as long as I can!
What do we do now, good lady knight?
Ready yourselves for battle and\nawait my word!
But first, bring shields for their arrows!\nPots, boards, furniture—anything that\ncan absorb incoming fire!
And make sure to move as a group!\nI don't want any stragglers!
Elisanne, take care of that group!
Sir, the villagers are on the move!\nThey appear to be commanded by\nthat knight we saw before!
Unleash your arrows on that rabble!\nI want them all feathered like hens!
The villagers are charging our position!
Such courage they show...\nMorale is truly a powerful force!
They've split our ranks in two!\nRetreat! All men, retreat!
Look! The Empire soldiers are fleeing!
We did it! We really did it!
We fought for our freedom and won!\nWe're finally liberated!
It is indeed a glorious day.
Good lady knight, you must let us\nshow you our appreciation.
I appreciate the gesture, but I have\npressing business elsewhere this day.\n...Sparrows! To me!
Stay here in case the Empire launches a\ncounterattack. Elisanne and I will hurry\nback and regroup with the main force.
A true soldier's work is never done.\nLet us be off, then!
